
1. Cause of ConcurrentModificationException

This exception occurs when a ArrayList is modified. During traversed.
Then java found ArrayList structure changed and throw Exception ConcurrentModificationException.


2. Exception throws in line number 142 because modified A

Most probably the code was removing elements from the same
list inside a for-each loop.

Example:

for (LoanAccount account : accounts ) {
    
        accounts.remove(account);
    
}

3. Minimal fix

Use Iterator.remove() instead of removing directly
from the list.

Example:






Iterator<Account>  acc=accounts.iterator();

while(acc.hasNext()){
 Account elements=acc.next();
 if(elements.Invaild){
  acc.remove;// safe remove
  
 }
 
}



